The Dragon is a yang substance but comes from the place of li (a yin kua： ☲).
The Tiger belongs to yin but is produced in the place of k’an (a yang kua： ☵).
The two things are able to reverse the ordinary process in such fashion that a
mother is born to her daughter. The five elements should enter wholly into the
central position.
